"Belastegui Macadam X.M., Del Prado A., Merino P., Estavillo J.M., Pinto M., González-Murua C.","Dicyandiamide and 3,4-dimethyl pyrazole phosphate decrease N<inf>2</inf>O emissions from grassland but dicyandiamide produces deleterious effects in clover",2003,"Journal of Plant Physiology","160","12",,"1517","1523",,,10.1078/0176-1617-01006,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0346687503&partnerID=40&md5=338d19c46a69627aa2871f8f0893c748","Dpto. Biol. Veg. y Ecología, UPV/EHU, Apdo 644, 48080 Bilbao, Spain; Inst. Vasco de Invest. Agraria, NEIKER, B Berreaga, 1, 48160 Derio, Spain; Inst. for Grass. and Environ. Res., IGER, North Wyke (Okehampton) EX20 2SB, United Kingdom","Belastegui Macadam, X.M., Dpto. Biol. Veg. y Ecología, UPV/EHU, Apdo 644, 48080 Bilbao, Spain; Del Prado, A., Inst. for Grass. and Environ. Res., IGER, North Wyke (Okehampton) EX20 2SB, United Kingdom; Merino, P., Inst. Vasco de Invest. Agraria, NEIKER, B Berreaga, 1, 48160 Derio, Spain; Estavillo, J.M., Dpto. Biol. Veg. y Ecología, UPV/EHU, Apdo 644, 48080 Bilbao, Spain; Pinto, M., Inst. Vasco de Invest. Agraria, NEIKER, B Berreaga, 1, 48160 Derio, Spain; González-Murua, C., Dpto. Biol. Veg. y Ecología, UPV/EHU, Apdo 644, 48080 Bilbao, Spain","The application of nitrogen fertilisers leads to different ecological problems such as nitrate leaching and the release of nitrogenous gases. N <inf>2</inf>O is a gas involved in global warming, therefore, agricultural soils can be regarded as a source of global warming. Soil N<inf>2</inf>O production comes from both the nitrification and denitrification processes. From an ecological viewpoint, using nitrification inhibitors with ammonium based fertilisers may be a potential management strategy to lower the fluxes of N<inf>2</inf>O, thus decreasing its undesirable effect. In this study, the nitrification inhibitors (NIs) dicyandiamide (DCD) and 3,4-dimethyl pyrazole phosphate (DMPP) have been evaluated as management tools to mitigate N <inf>2</inf>O emissions from mineral fertilisation and slurry application in grassland systems (experiments 1 and 2), and to assess the phytotoxic effect of these inhibitors per se on clover (experiment 3). Both nitrification inhibitors acted in maintaining soil nitrogen (N) in ammonium form, decreasing cumulative N<inf>2</inf>O emissions. DCD, but not DMPP, produced phytotoxic effects and yield reduction in white clover. A nutrient imbalance, which led to a senescence process visually observed as chlorosis and necrosis at the border of the leaves, was noted.","3,4-dimethyl pyrazole phosphate; Denitrification; Dicyandiamide; Grassland; N<inf>2</inf>O emission; Nitrification; Nitrification inhibitor; Nutrient imbalance; Phytotoxicity; Soil ammonium content; White clover","Enzyme inhibition; Enzyme kinetics; Gas emissions; Global warming; Leaching; Nitrogen; Nitrogen fertilizers; Reduction; Soils; Chlorosis; Grassland systems; Plants (botany); Medicago; Poaceae; Trifolium; Trifolium repens",,,,,,"Harwitte, W., (1980) Official Methods of Analysis. 13th Impression, pp. 127-129. , Association of Official Analytical Chemists, Washington; Barton, K., McLay, C.D.A., Schipper, L.A., Smith, C.T., Annual denitrification rates in agricultural and forest soils: A review (1999) Aust J Soil Res, 37, pp. 1073-1093; Britto, D.T., Kronzucker, H.J., NH<inf>4</inf>+ toxicity in higher plants: A critical review (2002) J Plant Physiol, 159, pp. 567-584; Davidson, E.A., Fluxes of nitrous oxide and nitric oxide form terrestrial ecosystems (1991) Microbial Production and Consumption of Green House Gases: Methane, Nitrogen Oxides An Halomethanes, , Rogers JE, Whitman WB (eds) Amer Soc Microbiol Washington DC; Estavillo, J.M., Rodriguez, R., Domingo, M., Muñoz-Rueda, A., Gonzalez-Murua, C., Denitrification losses from a natural grassland in the Basque Country under organic and inorganic fertilization (1994) Plant Soil, 162, pp. 19-29; Estavillo, J.M., Rodriguez, M., Lacuesta, M., Gonzalez-Murua, C., Effect of cattle slurry and mineral N fertiliser applications on various components of the nitrogen balance on mown grassland (1997) Plant Soil, 188, pp. 49-58; Estavillo, J.M., Merino, P., Pinto, M., Yamulki, S., Gebauer, G., Sapek, A., Corré, W., Short term effect of ploughing a permanent pasture on N<inf>2</inf>O production from nitrification and denitrification (2002) Plant Soil, 239, pp. 253-265; Frechilla, S., Lasa, B., Aleu, M., Juanarena, N., Lamsfus, C., Aparicio-Tejo, P.M., Short-term ammonium supply stimulates glutamate dehydrogenase activity and alternative pathway respiration in roots of pea plants (2002) J Plant Physiol, 159, pp. 811-818; Gonzalez-Moro, B., Lacuesta, M., Royuela, M., Muñoz-Rueda, A., González-Murua, C., Comparative study of the inhibition of photosynthesis caused by aminooxyacetic acid and phosphinothricin in Zea mays (1993) J Plant Physiol, 142, pp. 161-166; Kuenen, J.G., Robertson, L.A., Combined nitrification-denitrification processes (1994) FEMS Microbiol Rev, 15, pp. 109-117; Linzmeier, W., Gutser, R., Schmidhalter, U., Nitrous oxide emission from soil and from a 15N-labelled fertiliser with the new nitrification inhibitor 3,4-dimethylpyrazole phosphate (DMPP) (2001) Biol Fertil Soils, 34, pp. 103-108; Masclaux, C., Valadier, M.H., Brugiere, N., Morot-Gaudry, J.F., Hirel, B., Characterization of the sink/source transition in tobacco (Nicotiana tabacum L.) shoots in relation to nitrogen management (2000) Planta, 211, pp. 510-518; McTaggart, I., Clayton, H., Smith, K., Nitrous oxide flux from fertilised grassland: Strategies for reducing emissions (1994) Non-CO<inf>2</inf> Greenhouse Gases, pp. 421-426. , van Ham J et al (eds) Kluwer Academic Publishers, The Netherlands; McTaggart, I., Clayton, H., Parker, J., Swan, L., Smith, K.A., Nitrous oxide emissions from grassland and spring barley, following N fertiliser application with and without nitrification inhibitors (1997) Biol Fertil Soils, 25, pp. 261-268; Mena-Petite, A., Duñabeitia